pecies, pests, biological control agents, and more * Includes an annotated list of terrestrial and aquatic beetle habitats by season, information on starting and caring for a beetle collection, details on keeping beetles alive in the classroom, and a checklist of California beetle families  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAnimals. 4aGeneral. 4aNature. 7aNATURE / Animals.2bisacsh1 aEvans, Arthur V., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHogue, James N., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093756740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937567423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520937567/original  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles